		<h1>The data of my life</h1>
		<p>After developing a few dashboards for organizations I'm working with, I realized that I don't really have a personal dashboard. So, I started with the prerequisites for having a dashboard: defining goals, and finding ways to measure progress.</p>
		<h2>Goals</h2>
		<ul>
			<li>Run a half-marathon in 1:40 (that's a 7.5min/mile pace)</li>
			<li>Sleep 8 hrs/night (after a failed <a href="http://dustincurtis.com/sleep.html" title="I tried Everyman 3-Nap" target="_blank">Polyphasic Sleep</a> experiment)</li>
			<li>Reduce my intake of sugars to &lt;50g/day</li>
			<li>Respond to all e-mails within 24 hours</li>
		</ul>
		<h2>Measurement</h2>
		<ul>
			<li><a href="http://www.mdlabs.se/sleepcycle/" title="Sleep Cycle app for iOS" target="_blank">Sleep Cycle</a> alarm clock app</li>
			<li><a href="http://www.myfitnesspal.com/aerosuch" title="Food and Exercise diary" target="_blank">MyFitnessPal</a> app</li>
			<li><a href="http://kybc.org" title="Every 56 days!" target="_blank">Kentucky Blood Center</a></li>
		</ul>
